{{HydrocultureTOC}}
Roots must breathe oxygen. There is a limit to the amount of dissolved gasses that can be contained in water. [[w:Aquatic plant|Aquatic plant]] roots do not need direct access to oxygen in the water or medium, because these plants are [[w:Aerenchyma|adapted to transport oxygen throughout its physiological system]].

